-- Sri Lanka Signs $47 Million Water-Treatment Loan With Hungary
-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e
-- 2013-02-15T12:07:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-15/sri-lanka-signs-47-million-water-treatment-loan-with-hungary.html
Sri Lanka signed a 35 million-euro
($47 million) loan with Hungary’s Exim bank to rehabilitate
water-treatment plants that serve parts of the capital Colombo,
according to the finance ministry’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
